<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-1134 </DOCNO><TEXT>An automated system for adjustment, calibration and control of total absorptionCherenkov spectrometer is described. The system comprises a mechanicalplatform, capable of moving in two mutually perpendicular directions;movement detectors and limit switches; power unit, automation unit withremote control board. The automated system can operate both in manualcontrol regime with coordinate control by a digital indicator, and inoperation regime with computer according to special programs. The platformmounting accuracy is +- 0.1 mm. Application of the automated system hasincreased the rate of the course of the counter adjustment works 3-5times.</TEXT></DOC>